servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. In a #small pot{}, bring
@water{1 1/2%cups} salted to a boil. Halve, peel, and finely chop @shallot{1}. Mince
@garlic{2%cloves}. Roughly chop half the @basil{1/2%ounce} leaves. Halve
@lime{1}. Crush @peanuts{1%ounce} inside a #bag{} with a #mallet{} or heavy pan.
Mince @chili pepper{1}, removing ribs and seeds if you prefer less heat.

> HINT: Wash hands directly afterwards to avoid burning.

Add @jade rice{3/4%cup} to boiling water, cover, and simmer until tender,
~{13-15%minutes}.

== Crispy Green Beans ==

Trim @green beans{6%ounce} and toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of
@olive oil{2%teaspoon} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until slightly
crispy, about ~{12%minutes}.

== Pork Larb ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add shallots,
garlic, and as much Thai chili as you like. Toss until softened and fragrant,
about ~{3%minutes}. Add @ground pork{10%ounce} and increase heat to high.
Break up meat into tiny pieces until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> TIP: You'll want pieces broken up as small as possible for maximum flavor in every bite!

Season with salt and pepper.

Remove pan from heat. Stir in @sesame oil{1%tablespoon}, @soy sauce{1%ounce},
chopped basil, and @sugar{1/2%teaspoon}. Season with salt and pepper. Stir in
a squeeze of lime, to taste.

== To Serve ==

Plate: Serve pork larb on a bed of jade rice with crispy green beans. Sprinkle
with crushed peanuts and remaining basil.

> TIP: Tear any larger basil leaves.